This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a unified framework for neural net normalization, regularization, and optimization. It also investigates issues related to optimization and data dependence in neural networks. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as these fields heavily rely on neural networks and their optimization techniques.
